Statics: solving of ODEs I

E4.a - Task

  • given:

    • \(F, q_0, L, h, b, E\)

  • wanted:

    • normal (bending) stress \(\sigma(x,y)\)

    • deformation of the beam \(v(x)\)

    • maximal stress \(\sigma_{max}\) and maximal deformation \(v_{max}\)

  • procedure:

    • determine support reactions and internal force equilibrium

    • define stress and deformation equations

    • define boundary conditions

    • solve deformation equation using the defined boundary conditions

    • find \(v_{max}\)

    • find \(\sigma_{max}\)

    • plot configuration a) \(v(x)\) for, e.g., \(F \in {0 N, 100 N, 200 N, 300 N, 400N}\) considering \(L=100 mm, h=2 mm, b=15mm, E=210000 \frac{N}{mm^2}\)

  • pseudo-code:

Note

Do this task inside a jupyter notebook!

import sympy as sp
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

from IPython.display import Math, Latex

Define symbolic variables¶

In [24]:
L, F, x  = sp.symbols('L, F, x', real = 'True')
Ax, Ay, MAz = sp. symbols('Ax, Ay, MAz', real = 'True')
In [25]:
eq1 = sp.Eq(0 , Ax)
eq2 = sp.Eq(0 , Ay - F)
eq3 = sp.Eq(0, MAz - F*L)
In [26]:
sol = sp.solve([eq1, eq2, eq3],[Ax, Ay, MAz])
sol
Out[26]:
{Ax: 0, Ay: F, MAz: F*L}
In [27]:
Ax, Ay, MAz = sol.values()

Internal force reactions¶

Define symbolic functions¶

In [28]:
N = sp.Function('N')(x)
Q = sp.Function('Q')(x)
Mbz = sp.Function('Mbz')(x)

Set up equations¶

In [29]:
eq11 = sp.Eq(0, N + Ax) 
eq12 = sp.Eq(0, Q + Ay)
eq13 = sp.Eq(0, Mbz + MAz - Ay*x)

solve equations¶

In [30]:
sol = sp.solve([eq11, eq12, eq13],[N, Q, Mbz])
sol
Out[30]:
{N(x): 0, Q(x): -F, Mbz(x): -F*L + F*x}
In [31]:
N, Q, Mbz = sol.values()

Stress¶

In [32]:
E, h, b, y = sp.symbols('E, h, b,y', real = 'True')
In [33]:
Iz = b*h**3/12
In [34]:
sigma = -Mbz/Iz * y
display(sigma.subs([(x,0),(y,h/2)]))
$\displaystyle \frac{6 F L}{b h^{2}}$

Deformation¶

In [35]:
v = sp.Function('v')
In [36]:
eq = sp.Eq(sp.diff(v(x),x,x), Mbz/(E*Iz))
display(eq)
$\displaystyle \frac{d^{2}}{d x^{2}} v{\left(x \right)} = \frac{12 \left(- F L + F x\right)}{E b h^{3}}$
In [37]:
bc = {v(0):0, sp.diff(v(x),x).subs(x, 0):0}
In [38]:
sol = sp.dsolve(eq, ics = bc)
v = sol.rhs
display(sol)
display(sol.subs(x,L))
$\displaystyle v{\left(x \right)} = - \frac{6 F L x^{2}}{E b h^{3}} + \frac{2 F x^{3}}{E b h^{3}}$
$\displaystyle v{\left(L \right)} = - \frac{4 F L^{3}}{E b h^{3}}$
In [39]:
v = v.subs([(L, 100), (h, 2), (b, 15), (E, 210000)])
In [40]:
v_fun = sp.lambdify((x ,F), v, 'numpy')
s = np.arange(0,100,1)
In [41]:
plt.plot(s, v_fun(s,0))
plt.plot(s, v_fun(s,100))
plt.plot(s, v_fun(s,200))
plt.plot(s, v_fun(s,300))
plt.plot(s, v_fun(s,400))
plt.xlabel('x')
plt.ylabel('v(x)')
Out[41]:
Text(0, 0.5, 'v(x)')

def q(xL,xH):
    return sp.integrate(q0, (x, xL, xH))

eq2 = sp.Eq(0 , Ay - q(0, L))

E4.b - Task

A shaft inside a gear should be optimized. The solid (index S) shaft should be replaced by a hollow (index H) one.

  • given:

    • \(M_0, D, d, L\)

  • wanted:

    • ratio of mass of saved material \(\mu = \frac{m_H}{m_S}\)

    • stress increase \(\kappa = \frac{\tau_H}{\tau_S}\)

    • deformation increase \(\epsilon = \frac{\varphi_H}{\varphi_S}\)

    • find a new \(D_H\) considering a diameter ratio \(\epsilon=\frac{d_H}{D_H}\) and the condition that \(\tau_{Hmax} = \tau_{Smax}\)
